# Implementation Plan - Document Linking

## Goal Description
Ensure that when a file is attached during the "New Lot Registration" for a dump truck, the actual filename is linked to the lot data, and it is displayed correctly in the dashboard list.

## Proposed Changes

### Logic ([app.js](file:///c:/Users/tiesm/.gemini/antigravity/app.js))
#### [MODIFY] [app.js](file:///c:/Users/tiesm/.gemini/antigravity/app.js)
- **Submit Handler**:
    - Retrieve the file object from `#lot-truck-docs`.
    - Instead of pushing `{ name: '車両関連資料' }`, push `{ name: file.name, type: 'vehicle_doc' }`.
- **Render Logic ([renderBatches](file:///c:/Users/tiesm/.gemini/antigravity/app.js#417-449))**:
    - Update the `docBadges` mapping.
    - If `doc.type === 'vehicle_doc'` (or name check), render a `📎` icon.
    - Add a `title` attribute to the badge so hovering shows the filename.

## Verification Plan
### Manual Verification
- Open "New Lot Registration".
- Select "Dump" (Land).
- Attach a file (e.g., "shaken.pdf") to "Vehicle Related Documents".
- Register.
- In the dashboard list, check the "Type/Documents" column.
- Verify a 📎 icon appears.
- Hover over the icon and verify it correctly displays "shaken.pdf".
